The molecular weight listed in the excel file is 275.2989, but the molecular weight associated with the InChi string is 261.2717, according to what I found online. I did find a link that associates the name Glutarylcarnitine with that InChi string: http://www.chemnet.com/cas/en/109006-11-3/glutarylcarnitine.html. I googled Glutarylcarnitine  C12H21NO6 and found PubChem CID 53481622, which matches the formula and molecular weight but has a different InChi: InChI=1S/C12H21NO6/c1-13(2,3)8-9(7-11(16)17)19-12(18)6-4-5-10(14)15/h9H,4-8H2,1-3H3,(H-,14,15,16,17)/t9-/m0/s1. So it seems to me that either the InChi in the file is wrong, or else the Mass Formular and molecular weight are wrong.
